text: Snotra is a goddess of wisdom and prudence in Norse mythology. The Prose Edda says that Snotra is "high and courteous". She is a goddess that, according to Snorri Sturluson, "should be worshiped as a high-ranking goddess". She also is one of the few goddesses that dies during Ragnarok. Category:Norse gods and goddesses
title: Snotra
